reviews:
[{'name': 'Vegeta', 'text': 'the first time i went, the dc jack of my laptop was broken so i had it fixed for $120. fine. second time it wasnt working anymore after 6-8 months even after babying it like crazy so i went with the replacement jack and they discounted $20 for the part. so it was $100. fine. it stopped working AGAIN in a shorter time than before and on the third time, they still wanted to charge $120 even though i brought the part. i guess they were a bit greedy but still agreed to $100.

a while later they let me know that my motherboard is messed up and will cost me $450+ to fix it. ridiculous! so i took it back and dealt with the problem until i got a job at a cell phone repair place. they also fixed other electronics so i took my laptop there and after checking it over with my head tech, we found out how bad the job was done over the course of those three visits here. there was flux everywhere else on the motherboard (which would have eaten through but thankfully it didnt) and the soldering of the dc jack was terrible and obviously it wasnt working because the poor soldering lifted up and i had a dc jack halfway out! so we fixed it and at least i know itll last a good while because we cleaned it thoroughly, soldered it perfectly and with enough solder to keep it in place. finally, i realized i paid too much for these bad jobs considering how at my job, they charge $85 WITH labor, part, and a 6-month warranty!

do yourself a favor and avoid repair shops like these, you are better off going to a franchise repair shop where im currently in now. this shop is overpriced for poor repair jobs.', 'publishAt': '7 years ago', 'publishedAtDate': '2015-01-26T19:48:08.034Z', 'likesCount': 0, 'reviewId': 'ChZDSUhNMG9nS0VJQ0FnSURBOTZxWENBEAE', 'reviewUrl': 'https://www.google.com/maps/reviews/data=!4m8!14m7!1m6!2m5!1sChZDSUhNMG9nS0VJQ0FnSURBOTZxWENBEAE!2m1!1s0x0:0x7afd8c8d78f6c29c!3m1!1s2@1:CIHM0ogKEICAgIDA96qXCA%7CCgsI-LOapgUQgJmbEA%7C?hl=en-US', 'reviewerId': '102098967040909215002', 'reviewerUrl': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/102098967040909215002?hl=en-US', 'reviewerNumberOfReviews': 4, 'isLocalGuide': False, 'stars': 1, 'rating': None, 'responseFromOwnerDate': None, 'responseFromOwnerText': None}]

RESPONSE:

I did reach out and got no reply from your company. Since you are now charging for what you originally marketed as free features, to use your words from your crowd funding campaign “With Canary, the app and primary service are free,… Disrupting a broken system. We set out to disrupt the home security industry by designing a solution that addresses the major consumer pain points of existing products”.

You are correct, I can watch a live video feed and can watch videos up to 3 hours after they are recorded, but that is not very practical for a security device.

Judging from all the other negative reviews it looks like I am not the only person unhappy with this removal of what was originally promised.

To clarify, 24/7 watch live, motion notifications, geofencing are just some of the features that continue to be free and is still included as part of the Basic Service plan. In addition, we've added the Two-Way Talk feature to the free basic service plan. Two-Way Talk is a feature which has been heavily requested by our basic plan customers, and now everyone can stay even more connected to their homes by having real-time conversations through the Canary app.

For a long time, we offered many of our advanced features for free. Now, due to market changes, and consistent with our competitor’s offerings, we have adjusted our plans.

In addition, as you may see in the emails you’ve received, to assist you as our loyal customer with a smooth transition to our new plan, we are offering complimentary Premium Service for practically free of charge for an entire year. reviews: "[{'name': 'Marc', 'text': 'These days it\'s rare to have a relationship with a vendor that spans decades. This software is thorough, complete, easy to operate and largely bulletproof.  In addition there is nothing better than getting tech support from the guy who not only wrote the program, but is also a practicing doctor.  Dr. Schramm is a seasoned pro who understands all the needs and issues a Chiropractic, Medical, or Acupuncture office has and has built them into Handyworks.  Dr. Schramm is super knowledgeable in all aspects of computerizing your practice.  He handles all tech issues quickly and efficiently right over the phone or logs in directly.  He is constantly tweaking and improving the software and offers frequent upgrades through easy download. We chose Carecenta because we needed an integrated scheduling, billing and payroll software, and then found that Carecenta enables us to be in compliance with state and federal licensing regulations with our employees as well. We then discovered that Carecenta has a map-based caregiver search feature. I couldn’t believe it. We actually have a system that makes our agency unstoppable.

While on boarding is always difficult and overwhelming when switching providers, the customer service representative was immensely helpful.

When we experienced any bumps in the road, as any agency does, the customer service team has always been prompt to answer questions, research any issues or special requests that we might have.

Overall, it's a great software and Carecenta people were very helpful to ensure that we have a smooth experience, which is so important when you provide services."", 'publishAt': '6 years ago', 'publishedAtDate': '2016-10-01T20:07:17.622Z', 'likesCount': 1, 'reviewId': 'ChdDSUhNMG9nS0VJQ0FnSUNBbjRQUnJnRRAB', 'reviewUrl': 'https://www.google.com/maps/reviews/data=!4m8!14m7!1m6!2m5!1sChdDSUhNMG9nS0VJQ0FnSUNBbjRQUnJnRRAB!2m1!1s0x0:0xd787cff4fa7aa755!3m1!1s2@1:CIHM0ogKEICAgICAn4PRrgE%7CCgwI9a7AvwUQgO_LqAI%7C?hl=en-US', 'reviewerId': '115656576466489828272', 'reviewerUrl': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/115656576466489828272?hl=en-US', 'reviewerNumberOfReviews': 1, 'isLocalGuide': True, 'stars': 5, 'rating': None, 'responseFromOwnerDate': None, 'responseFromOwnerText': None}, {'name': 'Chari Zard', 'text': ""We purchased Carecenta home health software year ago after doing all of our scheduling manually and the office staff loves it! I’m not sure how we lived without it for so long. With Carecenta I can manage patient schedules electronically.
By using the intelligent case match engine feature like their Availability Search, I can now schedule the proper caregiver to the proper case. Then using the attendance verification telephony and GPS feature I know when each aide has started and when they finish their day. Having the ability to view the actions of my aides closely has improved the quality of my agency. Besides, it’s so easy to manage patient schedules. I can copy/paste appointments or add one on-the-fly from one screen.
Our schedulers would probably spend 70% less time scheduling after adopting Carecenta. Also, the replacements with real-time multiple caregiver offers done in minutes using text messaging and map features.
No more time wasted on turning completed appointments into invoices in Billing. All done automatically using electronic file, so the entire billing and payment consolidation takes literally few minutes per week. Most importantly we can bill Medicare electronically.
All 42 compliance items in Medical, Hiring, InService Classes and Evaluation tracked automatically for all your caregivers. No time spent on Payroll. I just select a week and click 'Send to payroll'. All done automatically. Just like in Billing.
Their reporting is awesome. I think we got somewhere around 150 reports. They came really handy during that DOH audit we had back in December.
Their training is very thorough and they have good responsive support team.
What's most important for me, Carecenta staff really takes care of you.
Now, the negative. Carecenta is a new software and they are adding new features like daily. So, I guess, there are bugs because of that. But they actually pretty good at troubleshooting the issues.
In terms of price, Carecenta is not cheap but you get to save so much time and don’t need to hire extra hands to handle your patients, billing or payroll. That’s a good thing, right?
Overall it's like day and night in running my business.  I give them 5 stars."", 'publishAt': '6 years ago', 'publishedAtDate': '2016-03-29T14:55:45.489Z', 'likesCount': 1, 'reviewId': 'ChZDSUhNMG9nS0VJQ0FnSUN3cF9YVUtnEAE', 'reviewUrl': 'https://www.google.com/maps/reviews/data=!4m8!14m7!1m6!2m5!1sChZDSUhNMG9nS0VJQ0FnSUN3cF9YVUtnEAE!2m1!1s0x0:0xd787cff4fa7aa755!3m1!1s2@1:CIHM0ogKEICAgICwp_XUKg%7CCgwI8a7qtwUQwJiW6QE%7C?hl=en-US', 'reviewerId': '107593482733560979462', 'reviewerUrl': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/107593482733560979462?hl=en-US', 'reviewerNumberOfReviews': 58, 'isLocalGuide': True, 'stars': 5, 'rating': None, 'responseFromOwnerDate': '2016-03-29T15:08:23.535Z', 'responseFromOwnerText': 'Thank you for the review and for sharing your experience with our homecare software.
